qgisprocess 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

Run algorithms using 'qgis_process'

Source: R/qgis-run-algorithm.R
qgis_run_algorithm.Rd

Run QGIS algorithms. See the QGIS docs for a detailed description of the algorithms provided 'out of the box' on QGIS (versions >= 3.14).

qgis_run_algorithm(
  algorithm,
  ...,
  PROJECT_PATH = NULL,
  ELLIPSOID = NULL,
  .raw_json_input = NULL,
  .quiet = FALSE
)

Arguments

algorithm

A qualified algorithm name (e.g., "native:filedownloader") or a path to a QGIS model file.

...

Named key-value pairs as arguments for each algorithm. Features of rlang::list2() are supported. These arguments are converted to strings using as_qgis_argument().

PROJECT_PATH, ELLIPSOID

Global values for QGIS project file and ellipsoid name for distance calculations.

.raw_json_input

The raw JSON to use as input in place of ....

.quiet

Use TRUE to suppress output from processing algorithms.

Examples

if (has_qgis()) {
  qgis_run_algorithm(
    "native:buffer",
    INPUT = system.file("longlake/longlake_depth.gpkg", package = "qgisprocess"),
    DISTANCE = 10
  )
}
